Kaplan–Meier survival curves (Fig. 3a
) were created with a sample size of 5 rats per group for a representation of the survival rate for the control and oxygen microfoam groups. A Log-rank (Mandel-Cox) test was done to compare the survival distribution of the oxygen microfoam group to the control group for a significant difference (α = 0.01). It was found that there was in fact a significant difference between the two groups (Χ
2 = 9.701, P = 0.002).
